# Ralph Handoff

## Last Run

2026-07-16_192241_repair

## Current Status

009B3A's validation repair is complete pending independent orchestrator revalidation.
`sap_workflow.models` owns the
existing SAP request and customer-code model state. One reversible state-only migration relocates
the historical model identities and their relation targets without executing any database schema or
data operation. The physical Finance-era tables, columns, indexes, constraints, rows, ids,
ciphertext, checksums, completion digest, delivery/task links, and audit/workflow identities remain
unchanged.

`finance.models` is now only a one-way compatibility import whose names are object-identical to the
canonical SAP classes. The public SAP module and loan-account relation consume the canonical owner.
Executable Finance request/delivery/completion policy intentionally remains for 009B3B.

The quarantined implementation was preserved. The six-error full-suite failure came from two older
historical migration tests allowing the new downstream SAP leaf to outrun their deliberately
reversed application schemas; their leaf exclusions now include `sap_workflow`. The independent
frontend failure came from the existing Node-only Playwright resolver being compiled through its
`src` unit test without Node declarations; a narrow compile-time declaration and optional
`globalThis.process` view fix it without changing browser-selection behavior or UI code.

